00:34:31,901 --> 00:34:33,891
如果半履带车能过
Our heaviest pieces of half-track

273
00:34:34,067 --> 00:34:35,001
其它车辆卡车也能
can make it, the others can.

274
00:34:35,004 --> 00:34:37,043
我知道卡车轮胎将会陷进沙里
I know the lorries wheel will bogged down but the half-track

275
00:34:37,192 --> 00:34:38,732
半履带车能控制住方向
with it's track can maneuver.

276
00:34:38,941 --> 00:34:40,517
你打算如何让卡车通过？
But how do you propose to get the lorries through?

277
00:34:42,191 --> 00:34:43,898
这个雷区布置有段时间了，上校
This is an old mine field, Colonel.

278
00:34:44,066 --> 00:34:46,602
地雷周围堆积了很多沙子，因而会形成马鞍状
The sand covering the mines had plenty of times to settle.

279
00:34:46,775 --> 00:34:48,394
只要停在斜坡上，我就能看清楚
By keeping to the slopes, I will be able to see

280
00:34:48,420 --> 00:34:49,880
地雷的准确位置
the depression over the mines.

281
00:34:50,065 --> 00:34:53,147
你难道想亲自去开路
So you intend to clear the way and pied piper us through?

282
00:34:54,065 --> 00:34:55,107
没错
That's right.

283
00:34:56,481 --> 00:34:58,104
- 泰恩军士长
- Sergeant Major Tyne!
- 长官
- Sir!

284
00:35:00,189 --> 00:35:02,938
你在后面负责做好车辆的伪装
Bring a drum from the lorries with branches and camouflage

285
00:35:03,106 --> 00:35:05,013
- 让大家在车上休息
- to wipe out our tracks.
- 长官
- Sir.

286
00:35:06,605 --> 00:35:08,430
这可不是件容易事
It may not be so simple.

287
00:35:08,813 --> 00:35:11,515
德国人总是布连环雷
The Germans often set their mines at tandem.

288
00:35:11,688 --> 00:35:13,892
